Online: 2013-09-03

Study on the Ship Arrival Pattern of Container Terminals DU Pengchenga, WANG Wenyuanb, TANG Guoleic, GUO Zijiand,
Faculty of Infrastructure Engineering, Dalian University of Technology, Dalian, 116024, China adupengcheng_1989@hotmail.com, bbsklwwy@gmail.com, ctangguolei@dlut.edu.cn, dzjguo@dlut.edu.cn

Keywords: Container ship; Arrival pattern; Liner routes; Distribution regularities.
Abstract. Container ship arrival pattern had an important effect on throughput capacity of container terminals. There is an urgent need for recognition of the ship arrival pattern of modern container terminal, owing to the change of the composition of both operating routes and arrival ships, which was brought up by the rapid development of China’s coastal ports container service. This paper statistically analyzes the ship arrival data collected from some domestic container terminals from the view of the number of daily arrival vessels and the inter-arrival time between two ships by using Chi-Square Test. The results prove that the ship arrival pattern of container terminals vary with the constitute of container liner routes, and the number of daily arrival vessels follows either Poisson or normal distribution, and the inter-arrival time follows both negative-exponential and gamma distribution.

Introduction
Container transportation of China’s coastal ports develops rapidly which contributes to China’s first position in global throughput ranking for many years, as well as its concentration on construction of more specialized container terminals. Since the imbalance of ship arrival is an important factor that affects the harbor traffic capacity, grasping the ship arrival pattern of container terminal is beneficial for deciding the scale of construction reasonably, attracting liner routes and improving competitiveness.
With the continued optimization of container berths, the development trend of large-scale ship is obvious and the constitution of container shipping routes and arrival vessels are changing. The current ship arrival pattern of container terminal should be updated urgently to meet the demand for development of modern container terminal. Therefore, this paper discussed the ship arrival pattern of container terminals derived by analyzing the ship arrival data of some domestic container terminals, so as to provide the basis to ascertain the throughput capacity and the scale of container terminals reasonably.

Statistic-testing Method
When the specific type of the overall distribution being studied is unknown, and only some certain assumptions can be put forward to represent the type or specific traits of the unknown distribution function, the analysis process can be called non-parametric assumptions, and the corresponding test methods are known as non-parametric hypothesis test. In this light, Pearson Chi-Square goodness of fit test can be used generally, and the test statistic can be calculated according to equation (1):

