port in South China whose routes reach more than 300 ports in over 80 countries and regions around the world. There are ocean routes like Red Sea routes, Europe routes, America routes, and Mediterranean Sea routes, and near-sea shipping lines like Southeast Asia routes, as well as domestic routes, feeder routes and inland river lines linking Hong Kong, Macao, and so on.
Take GOCT for example, this paper collects ship arrival data from April to December 2008, analyzes the ship arrival pattern of container terminals in Port GZ. The inspection results are shown in table 1.
(1) Distribution law of the number of daily arrival vessels Seen from table 1, the number of daily arrival vessels in GOCT follows Poisson distribution. And the histogram and fitting curve are shown in figure 2(a). (2) Distribution law of the inter-arrival time between two ships Table 1 shows that the inter-arrival time of GOCT follows both negative-exponential and gamma distribution, meanwhile the fitting degree of negative-exponential distribution is superior to that of gamma distribution. Moreover, the distribution histogram and fitting curve are shown in figure 2(b).

