Port JZ. Port JZ is a container feeder harbor in Bohai Rim region, with significant uncertainty of ship arrival influenced by its home port. It has opened up some container shipping lines. It owns domestic routes mainly and a small amount of feeder routes, but no routes for foreign trade. According to the ship arrival data from April to November 2008 of JNCT, this paper analyzes the ship arrival pattern of container terminals in Port JZ. The inspection results are shown in table 1.
(1) Distribution law of the number of daily arrival vessels Seen from table 1, the number of daily arrival vessels in JNCT follows Poisson distribution. The histogram and fitting curve are shown in figure 3(a). (2) Distribution law of the inter-arrival time between two ships Table 1 shows that the inter-arrival time of JNCT follows both negative-exponential and gamma distribution, meanwhile the fitting degree of gamma distribution is superior to negative-exponential. The distribution histogram and fitting curve are shown in figure 3(b).

