Port SZ. Port SZ is a container mainline harbor in Pearl River delta region, attracts hundreds of liner routes every week which are ocean shipping routes mainly. As one of the ports whose container throughput is the highest in single terminal, its container liner density ranks the first in China. The shipping services cover around the world, including ocean routes of America, Europe, Australia, Middle East, Africa and near-sea shipping lines of Southeast Asia. According to the ship arrival data of 2006 of YICT, this paper analyzes the ship arrival pattern of container terminals in Port SZ. The inspection results are shown in table 1.
(1) Distribution law of the number of daily arrival vessels Seen from table 1, the number of daily arrival vessels in YICT follows Poisson distribution. And the distribution histogram and the fitting curve are shown in figure 4(a). (2) Distribution law of the inter-arrival time between two ships Table 1 shows that the inter-arrival time of YICT follows both negative-exponential and gamma distribution, meanwhile the fitting degree of gamma distribution is superior to that of negative-exponential. The distribution histogram and fitting curve are shown in figure 4(b).

