Port YT. Port YT, as a container feeder harbor in Bohai Rim region, is in current contact for navigation and trading with more than 150 ports from over 100 countries and regions. It operates short-range ocean transportation and domestic trade, meanwhile feeds to the surrounding container mainline ports. It serves the near-sea shipping routes to Japan and Korea, as well as a few domestic routes to Qingdao, Yingkou and Shanghai.
Take DPWYT for example, this paper collects ship arrival data of 2008, analyzes the ship arrival pattern of container terminals in Port YT. The inspection results are shown in table 1.
(1) Distribution law of the number of daily arrival vessels Seen from table 1, the number of daily arrival vessels in DPWYT follows Poisson distribution. The distribution histogram and the fitting curve are shown in figure 5(a). (2) Distribution law of the inter-arrival time between two ships Table 1 shows that the inter-arrival time of DPWYT follows gamma distribution. The distribution histogram and fitting curve are shown in figure 5(b).

