To sum up, we could draw the following conclusions after analyzing the vessels arrival data of 6 container terminals mentioned above:
(1) The number of daily arrival vessels in majority of container terminals follows Poisson distribution. The imbalance of vessels arrival is great and the port operation assignment is difficult, because the foreign trade and domestic feeder both do coexist or the routes are affected by subjective berth designation in these ports. Most of our ports belong to this type, such as Port NB, GZ and JZ.
(2) The number of daily arrival vessels in small part of container terminals follows normal distribution. It’s easy to arrange the operation based on the relatively definite ship arrival in these container terminals which have relatively fixed routes. For example, the liner routes are dominated by ocean routes in Port SZ, and near-sea shipping lines in Port YT.
(3) The inter-arrival time between two container vessels is well fitted with negative- exponential and gamma distribution, besides the fitting degree of gamma distribution is superior to that of negative-exponential distribution.

Applied Mechanics and Materials Vols. 409-410

1203

Conclusion
This paper studies on the ship arrival pattern of container terminal to meet the development needs of the modern container terminal. According to the statistical analysis of the vessels arrival data of 6 container terminals, the ship arrival pattern of China’s container terminal is obtained as follows:
(1) The number of daily arrival vessels varies with the container shipping routes. It is Poisson distributed when the routes of domestic, foreign and feeder trade are all taken into account. While it follows normal distribution when the routes relative to a single.
(2) The inter-arrival time between two container vessels is well fitted with negative- exponential and gamma distribution, besides the fitting degree of gamma distribution is superior to that of negative-exponential distribution.
Literature References
Existing research have shown that it’s easy to arrange arrival vessels in specialized terminal or terminal mainly for liner routes since the ship and the owner of cargo are relatively concentrated. Therefore, it is generally believed that the inter-arrival time follows second order distribution of Ireland in consideration of the fact that ship arrival randomness is due to the natural factors [1]. Kozan established a container terminal queuing model based on the fact that the number of daily arrival vessels follows Poisson distribution and the inter-arrival time follows negative-exponential distribution [2]. Shabayek et al statistically analyzed the ship arrival data of Kwai Chung container terminals in Hong Kong from January 1999 to March 2000 and obtained the knowledge that the inter-arrival time follows negative-exponential distribution [3]. X.Y. Yang et al statistically analyzed the vessel arrival data of Yingkou container terminals from January to September in 2003 and Tianjin orient container terminals from August to December in 2003, and confirmed that the inter-arrival time follows negative-exponential distribution [4]. J.X. Liu et al statistically analyzed the ship arrival pattern of Tianjin port main channel from 2003 to 2005, including container ships, bulk cargo ships, ro-ro ships, etc., and received that the number of daily arrival vessels follows normal distribution [5].
